<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910712-0046</DOCNO><DOCID>910712-0046.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- WordStar International Inc.:   Software Concern Posts Loss   Of $1.8 Million for Quarter</HL><DATE>07/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   WDST</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   WordStar International Inc. reported a net loss of $1.8million, or 13 cents a share, for the third quarter ended May31, reflecting a one-time write-off of that same amount forresearch and development purchases related to the company'sacquisition of Lifetime Software.   Without the charge, the business software concern, basedin Novato, Calif., would have posted net income of $20,000.Year-earlier profit was $116,000, or one cent a share.Revenue rose 7.4% to $10.7 million from $9.9 million.</LP><TEXT>   During the third quarter, WordStar completed its purchaseof Lifetree Software, renamed the subsidiary Writing ToolsGroup, which recently acquired the exclusive retail rights tothe American Heritage Electronic Dictionary from HoughtonMifflin.   WordStar's board also voted to change the company's fiscalyear end from Aug. 31 to June 30, effective immediately.</TEXT></DOC>